article.headline: Blue, Quinn score 20 each
article.linkText: UCLA rely on Blue, Quinn to finish off Fresno St.
article.story:
FRESNO, Calif. (AP) -- Nikki Blue had 22 points and Noelle Quinn
added 21 as No. 18 UCLA defeated Fresno State 92-76 on Saturday
night.

Quinn also grabbed 12 rebounds for UCLA (6-1), which used a 16-3
second-half run to hand the Bulldogs (6-1) their first loss of the
season.

Fresno State's Mirenda Swearengin had 23 points, including 15 in
the first half. Swearengin was 9-of-20 from the floor, including
five 3-pointers.

After taking a one-point lead into the half, the Bruins put the
game away early in the second, opening with a 16-3 run to take a
55-41 lead.

The Bruins shot 58.1 percent (18-of-31) in the second half after
making just 37 percent of their shots before the break.

Lisa Willis added 18 points and Amanda Livingston chipped in
with 13 for UCLA.

UCLA came back from an 17-10 deficit to take a 39-38 lead at
halftime, the first time the Bulldogs have trailed at the break
this season.
